Folder contains functions (*.R) and data (*.csv) in WIDE MPL (minimum proficiency level) format:

update_mpl            pisa 2018 (reading, maths, science), pirls 2016
pirls_mpl             pirls 2006 and pirls 2011 data
timss19_mpl           timss 2019 (grade 4, grade 8, maths and science)
timss_mpl             timss 2011 and 2015 (grade 4, grade 8, maths and science)
pisa_mpl              pisa 2012 and 2015 (reading, science, and maths)
pisad_mpl             pisa-d data (reading, maths, and science)
sea-plm_mpl           sea-mpl 2019 (reading and maths)
pasec_mpl             pasec 2014 and 2019 (reading and maths, grade 2 and 6)
iso_code.csv          iso_code3 key variable 
ilsa_sum              function to calculate MPL in WIDE format

WIDE levels [here](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1UiSbvZDjUprnAHBNjaEZyoZzmxNXjDFe/edit?usp=sharing&ouid=113375079134992639300&rtpof=true&sd=true) 
